{
  "text": "The proportion of individuals with recent Abstinence in the current study (42%) was higher than the 10% with Abstinence in our follow-ups of COGA relatives and in the 25-year follow-up of men from the San Diego Prospective Study [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Those disparate proportions might reflect the older age of the current subjects, where Abstinence at an average of 60 requires survival to that age, and 24% of subjects selected for followup were deceased and are the focus of another paper.",
